## The Colorless Entry Tax at 3ct: $11,010 for an Invisible Difference

At 3ct, The Colorless Entry Tax reaches $11,010. The same grade difference that costs $260 at 1ct costs $11,010 at 3ct — because 3ct per-carat prices are dramatically higher and every grade step costs more per carat.

At 3ct, F color in a mounted platinum ring is still visually identical to G color. No observer can identify the difference. The $11,010 premium buys a GIA certificate designation.

| Carat | G Entry | F Entry | Colorless Entry Tax | Tax as % of G Price |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1ct | [$3,230](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29090690?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | [$3,490](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28215109?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | $260 | 8% |
| 2ct | [$16,490](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29307739?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | [$18,140](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29142126?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | $1,650 | 10% |
| 3ct | [$48,780](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/24964101?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | [$65,650](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29207723?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | $11,010 | 23% via VS1 comparison |

The percentage premium grows with carat weight — from 8% at 1ct to 10% at 2ct to approximately 20% at 3ct. This is because 3ct per-carat prices are 1.97× higher than 2ct per-carat prices, and the color grade premium scales with per-carat pricing.

3ct F stones on Blue Nile: [F-VS1 at $65,650](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29207723?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational), [F-VVS2 at $67,330](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29313489?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational), [F-VVS1 at $84,710](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29017695?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational).

